text:
York Street, west from West Broadway to St. Johns Lane, showing at the latter point the rear of St. Johns P.E. Church, which faced on Varick Street. Buildings appearing on the left are Nos. 10 to 2 inclusive, the 6-story structure being No. 6. On the right appear Nos. 7-5, 3 and 1. All of these buildings have disappeared, vacant lots occupying the York Street sites and a United States Post Office, the church site. The foreground of this view would be the present west side building line of the Sixth Ave. Extension.

About 1914.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

York Street, across west Broadway, east side, end of York Street. between Lespenard and Walker Streets.

P. L. Sperr
July 12, 1939
